  "description": "An oversized typographic hero with a three-row stacked headline, intentional row offsets, and two peeking rotated image cards. Built for editorial, fashion, and culture-led brands that want the type itself to be the visual.",
  "descriptions": {
    "descriptive": "Three large serif rows step diagonally — left-aligned, right-aligned, then indented again — with an italic accent on the middle row and an optional colored accent word. Two small image cards peek out from opposite quadrants on a slight rotation, breaking the symmetry without competing with the type.",
    "usage": "Best as a homepage opener for editorial brands, fashion houses, cultural institutions, music labels, and culture-led products where typography is the primary asset. Use peek images to suggest scope or season without committing to a hero photograph.",
    "audienceFit": "Reads as confident and current to design-aware audiences. Especially effective for brands targeting buyers who associate restraint, scale, and italic counterpoints with editorial credibility."
  }
